quran[20]{c,v,t,f}:
  15,32,"He said, “O Iblis<a class=""sup""><sup>e </sup></a>, what keeps you from being with those who prostrate themselves?”",footnotes:1:Iblis is another name of Satan or <i>Shaytan</i>.
  15,33,"He said, “Never would I prostrate myself to a human being whom You created from potter’s clay, of fermented mud.”"
  15,34,"He said, “Then get out of it{1}, for indeed you are an outcast,",footnotes:1:The Garden.
  15,35,"and indeed the curse is upon you until the Day of Recompense.”"
  15,36,"He said, “My Lord, then reprieve me until the day they are resurrected.”"
  15,37,"He said, “Then, you are indeed of the ones reprieved"
  15,38,"until the Day of the Time Appointed.”"
  15,39,"He said, “My Lord, since You have deluded me, I will most surely adorn for them<i class=""s"">(evil deeds) </i>on earth, and I will most surely delude them all,"
  15,40,"except for Your <span class="h">sincere chosen{1}</span>servants among them.”",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr, Ibn Amer and Ya’qub read it as: “…except for Your sincere servants…”</span>
  15,41,"He said, “This is a straight path <span class="h">which is binding on Me{1}</span>:",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “This is a high, straight path.”</span>
  15,42,"over My servants you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>have no authority indeed, except for those who follow you of the deluded ones."
  15,43,"And indeed, Hell is the meeting place for them all."
  15,44,"It has seven gates; for each gate is an assigned class.”"
  15,45,"Indeed, the mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>are amid Gardens and springs."
  15,46,"“Enter it in peace, feeling safe.”"
  15,47,"And We removed{1}whatever malice was within their chests—as brethren, on couches facing each other.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in past tense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  15,48,"No fatigue touches{1}them therein, nor from it will they ever be brought out.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense.
  15,49,"Inform<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>My servants that I—only I—am the Oft-Forgiving, the Bestower of mercy,"
  15,50,"and that My punishment is the painful punishment."
  15,51,"And inform them of the guests of Abraham,"
